      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy verification using manufactured solutions for the governing equations relevant to hemolysis prediction.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) was applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver and the scalar hemolysis transport equation. Observed order of accuracy (1.97 for velocity, 1.93 for hemolysis scalar) is consistent with the nominal second-order scheme. Code verification is satisfied at the required level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI reported for all five operating points; GCI below 5% for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study was conducted at all five operating points. Richardson extrapolation yields GCI values of 1.8%–4.3% for the hemolysis index across operating conditions. The discretization error is well-characterised and below the 5% threshold required at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
