      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or NRMSE) computed between CFD-predicted and experimentally measured hemolysis index at each operating point.",
      "rationale": "Normalised root-mean-square error across five operating points is 18.4% for the hemolysis index. While this exceeds the 15% informal target, the team notes that hemolysis index measurement variability (CV ~12%) accounts for a substantial fraction of the discrepancy. The comparison is considered adequate given measurement uncertainty."
