      "rationale": "The primary QoI in both validation and COU is the normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) computed identically. No surrogate quantities are used. QoI relevance is fully satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry and operating regime overlap with the COU device geometry and operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span 2–6 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM, covering the VAD operating envelope. Relevance of validation activities is satisfied."
    },
